        </article>

        <article>
          <h3><strong>Designer, Co-Founder</strong> at <em><a href="http://www.amoe.ba" target="_blank">Amoeba Consulting</a></em></h3>
          <span class="subheader">Oct 2012 - Sept 2013</span>
          <p>I played a key role throughout a client's product development cycle from initial rapid-prototyping
            through pixel-perfect implementation. By using best-practices in UX, UI, and Visual Design and cutting-edge
            frontend implementation -- I assisted clients to build out their products. By conceptualizing and testing the
            interaction between users and products I helped them to make products users don't have to think about.</p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h3><strong>Senior Designer</strong> at <em>TI Media</em></h3>
          <span class="subheader">Feb 2010 - Nov 2012</span>

          <p>Created and maintained layout and content on multiple consumer facing websites for mid-sized multinational with locations
            in San Francisco, New York, London, and Paris. Additionally, through online marketing efforts, I overhauled the company's email
            marketing presence, significantly increasing conversion. </p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h3><strong>Senior Designer</strong> at <em>Keiser Corp</em></h3>
          <span class="subheader">Sep 2005 - Jan 2009</span>
          <p>My first job right out of school and I wore many design hats -- from creation of print, multimedia, web, advertising,
            promotional, to customer support materials. Owned products; from initial creation, vendor acquisitions, print specification,
            prepress preparation, production, to distribution. Established and evolved design and branding; to increase
            market position, generate leads, and facilitate sales.</p>
